Business Brief -- Georgia-Pacific Corp.:
   Class-Action Dioxin Lawsuit
   Is Termed Without Merit
The company, which is pursuing appeals of both verdicts,
has said that its insurer refuses to cover the claims. That
means that Georgia-Pacific could face payments of more than
$4.2 million.
   Last week, a group of shareholders filed a class-action
suit against the company in U.S. District Court in Atlanta.
The suit, which seeks unspecified damages, alleges that
Georgia-Pacific failed to disclose "in a timely manner
litigation in the state courts of Mississippi. . . ."